rComments: I have Scott now at Hamline University. I'm taking his Filming Medieval China course and i hate it. Guess im not a film history guys.

Very hard class, but I actually enjoyed it.  I'm a history major so I was able to understand the class's emphasis on primary source material for the assignments. Probably wouldnt recommend this course for non-history majors OR people with no background whatsoever in Chinese studies, as it is quite tough.  But I personally found it interesting.

His lecture is not organized nor helpful. He attempts to touch on several ideas without repeating the assigned readings. As the result, his lecture contents randomly jump between different historic periods and are difficult to comprehend. Although he does offer help in online discussion board, you are likely to be on your own with your readings
